// FAQs about PPF
const faqs = [
  {
    question: "What is Paint Protection Film (PPF) and how does it work?",
    answer:
      "Paint Protection Film (PPF), also known as clear bra, is a thermoplastic urethane film applied to painted surfaces of a vehicle to protect from stone chips, bug splatter, minor abrasions, and environmental contaminants. Modern PPF features self-healing technology that allows minor scratches to disappear with heat application. The optically clear film is virtually invisible once applied and preserves your vehicle's appearance while maintaining its resale value. Our premium PPF products offer advanced stain resistance, UV protection to prevent yellowing, and hydrophobic properties that make cleaning easier.",
